---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - JamBuddy" description="Learn about the story behind JamBuddy and our mission to enhance musical creativity and collaboration.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gray-900 text-white py-20 rounded-lg">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">About JamBuddy</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        The ultimate music practice tool for musicians and music teachers - with real-time chord recognition, powerful practice features, and complete song organization
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 mb-2 text-center">
        <span class="inline-block bg-yellow-400 text-black font-bold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg shadow">
          Works offline – no ads, one-time purchase<br />
          Minimal latency chord recognition – Multi-instrument support<br />
          Built for musicians & teachers who want to <b>learn songs faster and teach more effectively</b>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Story -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6">My Story</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-300">
            <p class="mb-6">
              Hey! I'm Steve Ewing, the solo developer behind JamBuddy. I built this app because I'm learning guitar myself, having just picked up the ukulele last year. As a data scientist who's passionate about music, I wanted a tool that could help me identify chords in songs I'm trying to learn.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              While I'm comfortable with data analysis and machine learning, app development is completely new territory for me. JamBuddy represents my first foray into mobile development, applying my data science skills to audio analysis while learning Android development from scratch.
            </p>
            <p>
              JamBuddy is my attempt to solve a real problem I faced - a simple app that listens to music and tells you what chords are being played, whether you're practicing an instrument or just trying to figure out your favorite song. Perfect for beginners like me!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-purple-500/20">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-24 h-24 bg-indigo-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
              <svg class="w-12 h-12 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">My Goal</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300">
              To make learning instruments easier and more fun by helping people quickly identify chords in their favorite songs without needing years of ear training.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- App Principles -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900/80 rounded-lg mt-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">App Principles</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          What I care about when making JamBuddy
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Beginner Friendly</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Made for people like me who are just starting out and want to learn their favorite songs without years of ear training.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-green-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 3v4M3 5h4M6 17v4m-2-2h4m5-16l2.286 6.857L21 12l-5.714 2.143L13 21l-2.286-6.857L5 12l5.714-2.143L13 3z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Simple & Useful</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Focused on what matters: quick, accurate chord detection for any music you play or hear.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Constantly Improving</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            JamBuddy evolves every week, and your feedback helps shape its future.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the Developer -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg mt-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">About the Developer</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Just a student who loves music and coding
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-12">
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-8 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/20 max-w-2xl">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center text-left">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-600 to-gray-800 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">SE</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Steve Ewing</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 font-medium mb-4">Data Scientist & Music Enthusiast</p>
              <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
                I work as a data scientist and love exploring how machine learning can help musicians. JamBuddy is my first mobile app after picking up ukulele and guitar.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-300">
                When I'm not coding or practicing chords, I'm studying music theory and testing new ways to analyze audio.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- App Features -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg mt-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">What JamBuddy Can Do</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300">
          A few key tools that take the guesswork out of learning
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h1.586l4.707-4.707C10.923 3.663 12 4.109 12 5v14c0 .891-1.077 1.337-1.707.707L5.586 15z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">🎧 Real-Time Chord Recognition</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Detects chords instantly through your device's microphone with Circle of Fifths visualization, next chord prediction for jamming, and built-in chromatic tuner for guitar, bass, ukulele, mandolin & more
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">📚 Practice Tools for Every Skill Level</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Visual metronome with customizable light pulses, strum pattern display to improve timing & rhythm, audio speed control – slow down without changing pitch, and smart looping for tricky parts
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">✍️ Organize Your Songs & Lessons</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Store sheet music (PDF/images), backing tracks, lyrics, and chord charts. Add custom notes and annotations with fast access to large libraries. Multiple themes & custom color schemes with flexible layouts for phones and tablets.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">🎸 Multi-Instrument Support</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Supports guitar, bass, ukulele, mandolin, and baritone ukulele with optimized chord visualization for each instrument. Built for musicians & teachers who want professional-grade tools that work offline.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="relative py-24 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900 via-purple-900 to-blue-900 rounded-xl mt-8 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600/20 via-purple-600/20 to-green-600/20"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-white via-blue-100 to-green-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Get JamBuddy Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        JamBuddy is now available! Download the app and start learning your favorite songs today.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 justify-center">
        <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.jambuddy.app&hl=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group bg-gradient-to-r from-white/20 to-white/10 border-2 border-white/30 backdrop-blur-sm text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-2xl font-bold text-xl hover:from-white/30 hover:to-white/20 transition-all duration-300 flex items-center shadow-2xl transform hover:scale-105">
          <img src="/images/icons/google-play-badge.png" alt="Get it on Google Play" class="h-12 mr-4 transition-transform group-hover:scale-110" />
          Get on Google Play
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="bg-gray-800/80 border-2 border-gray-600 text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-2xl font-bold text-xl hover:bg-gray-700/80 hover:border-gray-500 transition-all duration-300 flex items-center backdrop-blur-sm transform hover:scale-105">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 mr-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
          </svg>
          Send Feedback
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>